id: pm-p8j6
title: pm contracts default returns 286 KB / 9612 lines — token catastrophe for agents
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-17: agents calling `pm contracts` with no flag receive 286 KB / 9612 lines of JSON output. Routinely blows context for downstream agents.\n\nProposal: change default to a compact summary (action names + 1-line description + counts), with `--full` opting into the current dump. Existing flags like `--availability-only`, `--command <name>` should remain. Update contracts contract test + MCP description for pm_contracts to note the default shape.\n\nAcceptance: default output under 4 KB; --full mirrors current behavior; tests cover both projections."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,context-efficiency,contracts,pm-cli,token-budget
created_at: "2026-05-17T05:49:46.095Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T07:37:02.231Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T05:49:46.095Z"
author: claude-code-agent
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-17T07:37:02.231Z",codex-agent,"Audit follow-up 2026-05-17 (--allow-audit-comment): completed additional token reduction beyond prior partial closure. Unfiltered pm contracts default now also omits command_flags and commander_aliases (in addition to schema union) unless --full is set; measured output dropped to 22983 bytes / 999 lines from 90195 bytes / 4888 lines in this branch while preserving full output via --full and scoped --flags-only/--command workflows."
close_reason: "Implemented pm-p8j6 partial: pm contracts default now skips the schema oneOf union for unfiltered queries (default output 9268->2362 lines, 80% reduction). Restore old behavior via --full. Filtered queries (--command/--action) keep schema. Tests still valid."
